{
  "name": "sunchamber",
  "description": "Bright chamber strings, pizzicato sparkling and soft arco glowing, sunlit and gentle. A small string ensemble both plucked (pizzicato, dry and bouncy) and bowed (arco, warm soft swell) — sunlit chamber music, elegant and tender, warm-bright and never severe. A round double-bass pizz grounds the room; a singing violin arco carries the melody while a viola pizz dances a counter-line; a warm cello glows in the middle; high violin harmonics chime, tiny top-string flicks sparkle with light echoes; a full arco ensemble blooms open, a tremolo-bowed chord shimmers, a col-legno tap keeps the pulse, and a bright pizz flick lifts as a tender accent. A major @ A=432, additive and clean, hall reverb, sunlit and never dreary.",
